CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 26, 1958, pg. A3 reads: " "Y" $40,000 Drive Begins - An interracial group of civic leaders met at the Homewood United Presbyterian Church last Sunday and began a drive to raise $40,000 for construction of a new building to provide adequate services for an expanding population in Homewood-Brushton area. Left to right: The Rev. J. A. William, the Rev. J.M. Findley Brown, W.T. Pitzer, chairman of the "Y" board and manager, Central Division, Westinghouse; the Rev. P.W. Phillips, James A.Traylor, "Y" director; the Rev. W.T. Petit and the Rev. Frank Felder.  The drive closes May 31. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left: Rev. J. A. William, Rev. J.M. Findley Brown, W.T. Pitzer, Rev. P.W. Phillips, James A.Traylor, Rev. W.T. Petit, and Rev. Frank Felder, in interior of Homewood United Presbyterian Church
